reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Duracell Ion Speed 1000 Battery Charger - A Must-Have for Every Household and Business!
reviews.reviewText: The Duracell Ion Speed 1000 Battery Charger is an absolute game-changer when it comes to powering household and business devices with AA and AAA batteries. This top-notch charger has exceeded all my expectations and has become an indispensable part of my daily life.First and foremost, the inclusion of four pre-charged AA rechargeable batteries is a huge plus. Having them ready to use right out of the box saved me time and money. The batteries hold their charge exceptionally well, providing long-lasting power for all my gadgets, toys, and devices. The reliability of Duracell is unparalleled, and these batteries are no exception.The Ion Speed 1000 Battery Charger lives up to its name, delivering lightning-fast charging times. With its advanced technology, it juices up my batteries in no time, ensuring that I never have to wait long to get my devices up and running. This feature has been a game-changer during emergencies or when I'm in a rush.The user-friendly design of the charger is another standout feature. The LED indicators make it easy to monitor the charging status, allowing me to know exactly when the batteries are fully charged and ready to use. Additionally, the smart auto shut-off function ensures that I don't have to worry about overcharging my batteries, promoting safety and prolonging the battery lifespan.The compact and sleek design of the Ion Speed 1000 Battery Charger is perfect for both home use and business trips. Its portability allows me to take it with me wherever I go, ensuring that my devices never run out of power when I need them the most.Duracell's commitment to sustainability also impressed me. By using rechargeable batteries, I'm reducing waste and contributing to a greener environment. It feels good to know that I'm making a positive impact on the planet with every charge.In conclusion, the Duracell Ion Speed 1000 Battery Charger is an absolute winner in every aspect. With its quick charging capability, reliability, user-friendly features, and environmentally conscious design, it has become an essential tool for every household and business. I highly recommend this product to anyone in need of a high-quality battery charger that delivers outstanding performance and is built to last. Five stars all the way!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic rechargeable batteries!
reviews.reviewText: I have been using the Duracell rechargeable brand for about 6 years now, and every new version is getting better. Mostly use these for flashlights and for small house plant irrigation units. They work great and always hold a respectable charge.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Recharger and rechargeable batteries
reviews.reviewText: I like Duracell products, and this recharger is no different. You will receive six rechargeable batteries with this purchase, 4 AA and 2 AAA. Works fine with quick recharge times. Duracell rechargeable batteries now look like their standard "coppertop" batteries, in small print you see they are in fact rechargeables. Fooled me when I first saw them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good basic battery/charger set up. Capacity good after nearly 2 years of use.
reviews.reviewText: The batteries are obviously lower capacity than other options but they do perform within reason against their specified 1300mah capacity. Keep in mind this is discharge capacity so actual usable capacity rather than the amount of power the battery accepts during charging. My measurements in the pictures are after nearly 2 years and probably ~30 cycles.So 5 stars for the batteries really, but the charger is 3 stars because you have to charge in pairs. Which is bad for the batteries, produces less consistent charge, and is inconvenient. Things I didn't realize are downsides when I bought it.So together the pair gets 3 stars.

reviews.reviewText: Finally a real solution to spending a lot of $$$$ on batteries for our TV remotes. These hold a charge very well and seem to last longer than a traditional battery.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I'm a fan of Duracell and prefer it over others. With time a lot of designs change. I had and still might, it could be someplace in storage, a different charging unit and it was better than this one for two reasons. The two prongs to plug in didn't rotate to hide (which is good for traveling and I understand the reason behind), which secured it in the wall better. Secondly, the batteries stayed in place better. I don't know if it's because the one I previously had was only for AA, where as this one is for both AA and AAA batteries.I use rechargeable batteries mainly for my Xbox controllers. I have 3 sets of AA rechargeable batteries and 1 set of AAA batteries. Which are used for the Roku/Firestick controllers.
